Grouping Different Elements in HTML code make up your page faster to load easier to customize and Maintain.
The <div> tag is a container tag that keeps your page organized.
Div Element is a block-level Element take up the full of available width.
The style in a <div> container will apply to all its nested elements unless you give them their own.
code:
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Document</title>
    <style>
        .one{
            color:brown;
            font-size:20px;
            border:2px solid;
        }
        .two{
            color:blueviolet;
            font-size:25px;
            border:3px solid;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="one">
        <h2>Div Class One</h2>
        <p>Grouping Different HTML elements code make your faster and load easier to maintain and Custom</p>
        <h3>Heading h3</h3>
        <p style="color:orangered">Lorem ipsum dolor sit, amet consectetur adipisicing elit. Quo illo impedit architecto voluptas dignissimos dolores corporis molestias qui necessitatibus, placeat ex nisi rem unde accusamus repudiandae soluta quisquam neque doloribus!</p>
    </div>
    <div class="two">
        <h2>Div Class One</h2>
        <p>Grouping Different HTML elements code make your faster and load easier to maintain and Custom</p>
        <h3>Heading h3</h3>
        <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit, amet consectetur adipisicing elit. Quo illo impedit architecto voluptas dignissimos dolores corporis molestias qui necessitatibus, placeat ex nisi rem unde accusamus repudiandae soluta quisquam neque doloribus!</p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
